\b\fs30 I. What Monetary Policy Cannot Do 
\b0\fs24 \

\b\fs30 From the infinite world of negation, I have selected two \up2 limitations \up0 of monetarypolicy to discuss: (1) It cannot peg interest rates for more than very limited periods; (2) It cannot peg the rate of unemployment for more than very limited periods. I select these because the \up2 contrary \up0 has been or is widely believed, because they correspondto the two \up2 main \up0 unattainable tasks that are at all likely to be assigned to monetary \up2 pol- \dn3 icy, and \up0 because essentially the same theoretical analysis covers \up2 both. 
\b0\fs24 \up0 \

